DescripcionEs:
Sintaxis:
FOR var FROM inicio TO (o DOWNTO) fin [STEP incremento] DO comandos END;

Establece la variable var en inicio; luego, mientras el valor de esta variable sea igual o menor que (o más que en un DOWNTO) fin, ejecuta comandos y suma (o resta DOWNTO) 1 (o incremento) a var. 

Ejemplos:
//print  1 3 5 7 9
FOR A FROM 1 TO 10 STEP 2
  DO
  PRINT(A); 
END;


//print  10 8 6 4 2
FOR A FROM 10 DOWNTO 1 STEP 2
  DO
  PRINT(A); 
END;

DescripcionEn:
Syntax:
FOR var FROM start TO (or DOWNTO) finish [STEP increment] DO commands END;

Sets variable var to start; then, for as long as this variable’s value is less than or equal to (or more than for a DOWNTO) finish, executes  commands and adds (or subtracts for DOWNTO) 1 (or increment) to var. 

Examples:
//print  1 3 5 7 9
FOR A FROM 1 TO 10 STEP 2
  DO
  PRINT(A); 
END;


//print  10 8 6 4 2
FOR A FROM 10 DOWNTO 1 STEP 2
  DO
  PRINT(A); 
END;

